Elements.Description: My child felt as if he/she needed to move his/her legs a lot.
A sudden noise made my child jump.
My child could not stay still for long.
My child's breathing was fast, even when he/she was not exercising or playing hard.
My child was sweaty, even when he/she was not exercising or playing hard.
My child's heart pounded, even when he/she was not exercising or playing hard.
My child's heart beat faster than usual, even when he/she was not exercising or playing hard.
My child had trouble breathing, even when he/she was not exercising or playing hard.
My child had a bad stomach ache.
My child had pain that really bothered him/her.
My child felt some food coming up into his/her throat.
My child had trouble staying asleep.
